            <scopecontent id="aspace_90cc1cb5716ecc3eda5186c9d4920ac9">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Series I. contains separate files for Raymond Queneau and Jean-Pierre Faure correspondence from the Collège de 'Pataphysique. The bulk of the correspondence to Queneau, received during his tenure with the Collège as "Transcendental Satrap" from the early 1950s through early 1970s, is from Jean-Hugues Sainmont, pseudonym of Emmanuel Peillet; most of the correspondence is also signed by Sainmont with another pseudonym ("Latis"). Other correspondents include Henri Bouché, Jean Ferry, Raymond Fleury, Thiéri Foulc, and later, to Faure, bookseller Sylvain Goudemare. Material also mentions Alfred Jarry, Baron Jean Mollet, Boris Vian, and Noël Arnaud.</p>
               <p>In addition to these larger files, there is one autograph manuscript postcard signed from Alfred Jarry to Gustave Kahn.</p>
            </scopecontent>
